The paper discusses the fundamental concepts of Big Data, its storage, and the MapReduce programming paradigm used in processing large datasets, which are all related to database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions concerns related to privacy and security, which fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of Big Data Analytics in making better business decisions, which is related to the field of information retrieval (cs.IR). The two case studies presented in the paper also involve social networks and the Internet of Things, which are related to the field of social informatics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper briefly touches on data representation, which could fall under the category of cryptography (cs.CR).
